**U.S. Law Knowledge Graph**

Validation Spec • Version 0.5 (Draft)

*Document 2 of 4 --- All validation rules, error codes, and validator
implementation guidance*

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **VERSION 0.5 --- WHAT CHANGED FROM v0.4**                            |
|                                                                       |
| Fix 1: E018 added. New error code for PRECONDITION_TO validation:    |
| source must be Doctrine, target must be Doctrine or DoctrinalTest,   |
| condition_note is required.                                           |
|                                                                       |
| Fix 2: Compatibility matrix updated. PRECONDITION_TO added as valid  |
| edge type with Doctrine -> Doctrine | DoctrinalTest.                  |
|                                                                       |
| Fix 3: opinion_ref.opinion_type enum updated (Section 2.6). Added    |
| 'majority' as valid opinion_type for INTELLECTUALLY_PRECEDES.         |
|                                                                       |
| Fix 4: overrule_type enum updated (Section 2.4). Added 'partial' as  |
| valid overrule_type for OVERRULES. Requires notes when partial is    |
| used.                                                                 |
|                                                                       |
| Fix 5: Area required fields updated (Section 1.2). jurisdiction[] and|
| tier now trigger E001 if missing (previously WARNING only).           |
|                                                                       |
| Fix 6: DoctrinalTest required fields updated (Section 1.5).          |
| source_case_id, scrutiny_level, burden, and test_form now required   |
| at top-level node; E001 if missing.                                   |
|                                                                       |
| Fix 7: E019 added. Partial overrule without notes triggers error.    |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **PURPOSE**                                                           |
|                                                                       |
| This document is the authoritative reference for the validation       |
| layer. Every rule here must be implemented in the validator.          |
|                                                                       |
| Rules are classified as ERROR (rejects the addition) or WARNING       |
| (flags for contributor review, does not reject).                      |
|                                                                       |
| The validator runs on every proposed addition, whether from a human  |
| contributor or an automated pipeline.                                 |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

**1. Node Validation**

**1.1 Universal rules (all node types)**

> * [ERROR] All required attributes must be present and non-empty
>
> * [ERROR] id must be globally unique across all node types
>
> * [ERROR] id must match the slug format: lowercase_snake_case, no
> special characters, max 80 chars
>
> * [ERROR] valid_until must be null or a date strictly after valid_from
>
> * [ERROR] status must be a defined enum value for that node type
>
> * [ERROR] jurisdiction must contain at least one value
>
> * [ERROR] No two nodes may share a display label across any node type

**1.2 Area**

> * [ERROR] parent_id must reference an existing Area node (except root
> where parent_id is null)
>
> * [ERROR] If parent_id is set, a CHILD_OF edge with matching
> source/target must exist
>
> * [ERROR] If a CHILD_OF edge exists, parent_id must match the edge's
> target_id
>
> * [ERROR] jurisdiction[] must be present and non-empty --- New in v0.5
>
> * [ERROR] tier must be present and be a non-negative integer --- New in v0.5
>
> * [WARNING] tier should equal parent.tier + 1

**1.3 Doctrine**

> * [ERROR] area_id must reference an existing Area node
>
> * [WARNING] label must not duplicate the parent Area's label
>
> * [WARNING] If pending_establishment[] is non-empty and two slices
> have been added since the entry was created, flag as stale (W002)

**1.4 Case**

> * [ERROR] decided_date must be a valid date not in the future
>
> * [ERROR] court_level must be a defined enum value
>
> * [ERROR] opinion_form must be a defined enum value
>
> * [ERROR] procedural_disposition must be a defined enum value
>
> * [ERROR] holding_type must be affirmative or by_negation
>
> * [ERROR] If per_curiam: true, majority_author must be null (E017)
>
> * [ERROR] If per_curiam: false, majority_author must not be null
> (E017)
>
> * [ERROR] If opinion_form is per_curiam, per_curiam must be true
>
> * [WARNING] precedential_weight should be consistent with court_level
> + status. If court_level is district and precedential_weight is
> binding, flag as inconsistent (W004)
>
> * [WARNING] If status is mooted or cert_denied, precedential_weight
> should be none

**1.5 DoctrinalTest**

> * [ERROR] prongs must contain at least two elements
>
> * [ERROR] source_case_id must reference an existing Case node
>
> * [ERROR] An ESTABLISHES edge must exist from source_case_id to this
> DoctrinalTest --- canonical field check (E013)
>
> * [ERROR] If source_case_id and the ESTABLISHES edge disagree, reject
> with: "source_case_id and ESTABLISHES edge are inconsistent. Edge is
> canonical." (E013)
>
> * [ERROR] Any prong with contested: true must have a non-empty
> contest_note
>
> * [ERROR] scrutiny_level must be present and a defined enum value ---
> New in v0.5
>
> * [ERROR] burden must be present and a defined enum value --- New in
> v0.5
>
> * [ERROR] test_form must be present and a defined enum value --- New
> in v0.5
>
> * [WARNING] If pending_establishment[] is non-empty and two slices
> have been added since the entry was created, flag as stale (W002)

**1.6 ConstitutionalProvision**

> * [ERROR] provision_type must be present and one of: amendment |
> section | clause | article --- New in v0.5
>
> * [ERROR] text must be present and non-empty
>
> * [ERROR] ratified_date must be a valid date

**2. Edge Validation**

**2.1 Universal rules (all edge types)**

> * [ERROR] source_id must reference an existing node or a declared
> cross-slice dependency
>
> * [ERROR] target_id must reference an existing node or a declared
> cross-slice dependency
>
> * [ERROR] Source and target node types must be compatible with the
> edge type (see compatibility matrix, Section 2.8)
>
> * [ERROR] No duplicate edges: same source_id, target_id, and edge_type
> within the same validity window
>
> * [ERROR] id must be globally unique and match slug format

**2.2 CHILD_OF**

> * [ERROR] Graph must remain a DAG after insertion --- no cycles
>
> * [ERROR] Each non-root Area node may have at most one CHILD_OF edge
>
> * [ERROR] target must be an Area node

**2.3 MODIFIES**

> * [ERROR] direction attribute must be present
>
> * [ERROR] direction must be one of: narrows | expands | clarifies |
> complicates | repudiates | extends
>
> * [ERROR] MODIFIES and APPLIES edges must not both exist between the
> same source and target --- MODIFIES subsumes APPLIES (E011)

**2.4 OVERRULES**

> * [ERROR] overrule_type must be present: explicit | implicit |
> effective | partial --- partial is New in v0.5
>
> * [ERROR] target Case decided_date must be strictly before source Case
> decided_date
>
> * [ERROR] If overrule_type is partial, notes must be non-empty
> describing the scope of the overruling --- New in v0.5 (E019)
>
> * [WARNING --- cascade check] When an OVERRULES edge is added, surface
> a list of all Doctrine and DoctrinalTest nodes ESTABLISHED by the
> overruled Case. Require contributor to confirm: (a) each also needs an
> OVERRULES edge, or (b) the doctrine survives the overruling. This is a
> warning, not an error (W001).

**2.5 CIRCUIT_SPLIT**

> * [ERROR] source and target must both be Case nodes
>
> * [ERROR] source.court_level and target.court_level must both be
> circuit
>
> * [ERROR] source.court_name and target.court_name must differ

**2.6 INTELLECTUALLY_PRECEDES**

> * [ERROR] opinion_ref attribute must be present
>
> * [ERROR] opinion_ref.opinion_type must be: dissent | concurrence |
> plurality | majority --- majority is New in v0.5
>
> * [ERROR] source Case decided_date must be strictly before target Case
> decided_date

**2.7 PRECONDITION_TO --- New in v0.5**

> * [ERROR] source must be a Doctrine node (E018)
>
> * [ERROR] target must be a Doctrine or DoctrinalTest node (E018)
>
> * [ERROR] condition_note attribute must be present and non-empty (E018)

**2.8 Historical edges**

> * [WARNING] A GOVERNED_BY edge with valid_until populated should have
> a corresponding OVERRULES or MODIFIES edge on the governing
> Doctrine/Test that explains its termination (W003)
>
> * [WARNING] Any edge where valid_until is before 1900 should be
> reviewed --- likely a data entry error

**2.9 Edge type compatibility matrix**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Edge Type**           **Source -> Target**             **Notes**
  ----------------------- -------------------------------- --------------------------
  CHILD_OF                Area -> Area

  RELATED_TO              Area -> Area                     3-condition editorial test
                                                           required

  INCORPORATES            ConstitutionalProvision ->
                          ConstitutionalProvision

  GROUNDED_IN             Area or Doctrine ->
                          ConstitutionalProvision

  GOVERNED_BY             Area -> Doctrine or              condition optional
                          DoctrinalTest

  ESTABLISHES             Case -> Doctrine or
                          DoctrinalTest

  APPLIES                 Case -> Doctrine or              Not allowed when MODIFIES
                          DoctrinalTest                    exists for same source/target

  MODIFIES                Case -> Doctrine or              direction required
                          DoctrinalTest

  OVERRULES               Case -> Case                     overrule_type required;
                                                           target must predate source

  INTERPRETS              Case ->
                          ConstitutionalProvision

  DISTINGUISHES           Case -> Case

  CIRCUIT_SPLIT           Case -> Case                     Both must be circuit-level;
                                                           different courts

  INTELLECTUALLY_PRECEDES Case -> Case                     opinion_ref required;
                                                           source must predate target

  PRECONDITION_TO         Doctrine -> Doctrine or          condition_note required;
                          DoctrinalTest                    New in v0.5
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**3. Graph-Level Validation**

> * [ERROR] The Area taxonomy must form a valid DAG --- no cycles in
> CHILD_OF edges
>
> * [ERROR] Every non-root Area node must have exactly one CHILD_OF edge
>
> * [ERROR] Every DoctrinalTest node must have at least one ESTABLISHES
> edge from a Case node
>
> * [ERROR] No orphan nodes --- every node must have at least one edge
>
> * [ERROR] No two nodes across any type may share a display label
>
> * [ERROR] parent_id / CHILD_OF consistency --- every parent_id must
> have a matching CHILD_OF edge and vice versa
>
> * [ERROR] source_case_id / ESTABLISHES consistency --- every
> DoctrinalTest.source_case_id must match its ESTABLISHES edge source

**4. Error Code Reference**

  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Code**    **Meaning**                  **Notes**
  ----------- ---------------------------- ----------------------------------------
  E001        Missing required field       {field} is required on {node_type} but
                                           is absent

  E002        ID not unique                ID {id} already exists on node type
                                           {type}

  E003        Invalid slug format          ID {id} contains invalid characters or
                                           exceeds 80 chars

  E004        Label collision              Label {label} already used by
                                           {existing_node_id}

  E005        Broken reference             {field} references {id} which does not
                                           exist

  E006        Type incompatibility         Edge {edge_type} cannot connect
                                           {source_type} to {target_type}

  E007        Duplicate edge               Edge {type} from {source} to {target}
                                           already exists in this validity window

  E008        MODIFIES missing direction   MODIFIES edge {id} has no direction
                                           attribute

  E009        OVERRULES missing            OVERRULES edge {id} has no overrule_type
              overrule_type

  E010        Chronology violation         OVERRULES/INTELLECTUALLY_PRECEDES:
                                           source must postdate target

  E011        APPLIES+MODIFIES collision   {source} -> {target} has both APPLIES
                                           and MODIFIES

  E012        parent_id/CHILD_OF mismatch  parent_id {pid} has no matching CHILD_OF
                                           edge or CHILD_OF edge disagrees

  E013        source_case_id/ESTABLISHES   source_case_id {cid} has no matching
              mismatch                     ESTABLISHES edge or edge disagrees

  E014        Cycle in DAG                 Adding this CHILD_OF edge would create a
                                           cycle

  E015        Multiple CHILD_OF            Area {id} already has a CHILD_OF edge

  E016        Orphan node                  Node {id} has no edges after insertion

  E017        per_curiam inconsistency     per_curiam:true but majority_author is
                                           set, or per_curiam:false but
                                           majority_author is null

  E018        PRECONDITION_TO violation    Source must be Doctrine; target must be  |
                                           Doctrine or DoctrinalTest;               |
                                           condition_note required. New in v0.5

  E019        Partial overrule without     OVERRULES edge has overrule_type:partial  |
              scope note                   but notes field is empty. New in v0.5

  W001        Cascade check required       OVERRULES edge added: check Doctrines
                                           established by {overruled_case}

  W002        Stale pending_establishment  pending_establishment entry {case_id}
                                           not resolved after 2 slices

  W003        Historical edge without      GOVERNED_BY with valid_until has no
              termination                  corresponding terminating event

  W004        precedential_weight          precedential_weight {pw} appears
              inconsistency                inconsistent with court_level {cl}
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

